      • addCurrentUser

        public void addCurrentUser()
        addCurrentUser This routine is used to add a user to the file of current users.

      • getUser

        public static User getUser(int reportsID)
        getUser This routine is used to add a create a user object from the file of current users, if the user is currently logged in. This routine will not return an User object if the user has timed out, or is no longer in the file.
        Parameters:
        reportsID - the current report
        Returns:
        User the user object

      • isValidUser

        public int isValidUser()

      • isValidUser

        public static int isValidUser(int reportsID)
        isValidUser This routine just takes the userID (aka reportsID) as input
        Parameters:
        reportsID - user id
        Returns:
        int returns VALIDENTRY if valid user, else INVALIDENTRY

      • UserTimedOut

        private static boolean UserTimedOut(int reportsID,
                                    java.lang.String loginDateStr)
        UserTimedOut This routine determines if the user has timed out. The input date string is taken from the file of current users. The routine needs to parse this, add on the timeout value, and then compare to the current time to determine if the timout period has elapsed.
        Parameters:
        reportsID - id of report
        loginDateStr - input data string
        Returns:
        boolean true if user has timed out

      • removeUser

        public static int removeUser(int reportsID)
        removeUser This routine is used to remove a user from the file of current users.
        Parameters:
        reportsID - id of report
        Returns:
        int report ID on success, -2 on error
